However, things get more interesting when considering a shmem page *in* the swap cache.  Here, `folio_mapping(folio)` resolves to `&swap_space`, so `shmem_mapping(&swap_space)` is FALSE, and `folio_test_anon` is also FALSE (since mapping is `&swap_space`). If such a dirty shmem page is in the swap cache, then the new logic dictates that it *is* skipped.

