For a dirty shmem page, I have to figure out what `mapping` is. If the shmem page is in the page cache, the mapping will be the shmem inode's mapping. In this case, `shmem_mapping(mapping)` returns `true`. The entire check therefore becomes `false`. The page is *not* skipped.

