So, in the swap cache case, `mapping` is `&swap_space`, `!shmem_mapping(mapping)` is `true`, and `!folio_test_anon(folio)` is `true` as well. Therefore this check is going to be *passed*. But! Now there is `folio_test_dirty(folio)`. If it is dirty, then `isolate_folio` returns false, it will *not* isolate it if it is dirty in swap space. This appears correct, and is consistent with the behavior of regular swap.


